Description: Neck sherd of Milesian Fikellura pottery oinochoe; dull white slip; interior: streaky brown; exterior: part of a painted rosette with added red on alternate petals and dots between petals at outer edge; trace of another ornament at top of sherd; inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: The number in Petrie's catalogue, '328', written on the exterior of the sherd.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 328)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 670, no. 289)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GF.108)
